\q1 It was silent and then I heard a voice:
\q1
\v 17 ‘Can a mortal \add human\add* be innocent before God?
\q1 Can a person be more pure than the creator of people?‘\f + \fr 4:17 \ft All speech marks in Bible translations are added by the translators. It’s not certain from the text whether or not this was what ‘the voice’ said, and if it is (as we assumed), it’s not clear where ‘the voice’ stopped speaking and Elifaz resumes. (Many translations put it at the end of the chapter, but remember that chapter breaks are also rather arbitrary and not in the original manuscripts.)\f*
