\q1
\v 4 Because the arrows of \add God\add* the provider are in me.
\q1 My spirit is drinking in their poison.
\q1 God’s terrors are set out against me.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \add Does\add* a wild donkey bray \add when it has\add* fresh grass \add to eat\add*,
\q1 or a ox bellow \add when it has\add* its fodder?
\q1
